Patch summary:
Keep gfxstream's advertised Vulkan contract consistent with the device it can
create. VulkanBatchedDescriptorSetUpdate deliberately masks inlineUniformBlock,
but inlineUniformBlock is mandatory for every Vulkan 1.3 device. Disable the
batching optimization by default so the already-supported non-batched inline
uniform path remains available.

Also classify VK_EXT_external_memory_acquire_unmodified as an emulated device
extension. The Android guest advertises this profile marker when a host driver
does not provide it because imported AHB layouts are already preserved in the
guest. It has no commands or feature/property structs, so forwarding the
enabled extension to such a host only makes vkCreateDevice fail with
VK_ERROR_EXTENSION_NOT_PRESENT (notably on Mesa Honeykrisp).

diff --git a/host/virtio_gpu_gfxstream_renderer.cpp b/host/virtio_gpu_gfxstream_renderer.cpp
--- a/host/virtio_gpu_gfxstream_renderer.cpp
+++ b/host/virtio_gpu_gfxstream_renderer.cpp
@@ -108,8 +108,10 @@
     GFXSTREAM_SET_BOOL_FEATURE_ON_CONDITION(
         &features, Vulkan,
         rendererFlags & STREAM_RENDERER_FLAGS_USE_VK_BIT);
+    // The batched descriptor path cannot represent inline uniform blocks, a
+    // mandatory Vulkan 1.3 feature. Prefer the compliant non-batched path.
     GFXSTREAM_SET_BOOL_FEATURE_ON_CONDITION(
-        &features, VulkanBatchedDescriptorSetUpdate, true);
+        &features, VulkanBatchedDescriptorSetUpdate, false);
     GFXSTREAM_SET_BOOL_FEATURE_ON_CONDITION(
         &features, VulkanIgnoredHandles, true);
     GFXSTREAM_SET_BOOL_FEATURE_ON_CONDITION(
diff --git a/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp b/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp
--- a/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp
+++ b/host/vulkan/vk_decoder_global_state.cpp
@@ -148,6 +148,7 @@
     "VK_FUCHSIA_external_memory",
     "VK_FUCHSIA_external_semaphore",
     VK_EXT_DEVICE_MEMORY_REPORT_EXTENSION_NAME,
+    VK_EXT_EXTERNAL_MEMORY_ACQUIRE_UNMODIFIED_EXTENSION_NAME,
     VK_EXT_QUEUE_FAMILY_FOREIGN_EXTENSION_NAME,
     VK_KHR_EXTERNAL_MEMORY_EXTENSION_NAME,
     VK_KHR_EXTERNAL_SEMAPHORE_EXTENSION_NAME,
